7hinlXft12NLGgUp1Rgcp1FMwwgDKDOxzPZy40ul2c5E_6orI0-b6hGH9dAFPXN_6oEndDulBaJ5hR0eH\",\"summary\":[]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Refined the dedicated active-class coverage test so `CompressionCodecName.getHadoopCompressionCodecClass()` now resolves successfully instead of only probing a missing optional class.\n\nChanges made:\n\n- Added `CompressionCodecNameTest.java`\n  - Exercises `CompressionCodecName.fromParquet(CompressionCodec.GZIP)`\n  - Calls `getHadoopCompressionCodecClass()`\n  - Asserts the resolved class matches the expected codec class\n\n- Added a minimal test-scope `org.apache.hadoop.io.compress.GzipCodec`\n  - Lets the public Parquet API’s `Class.forName(String)` path succeed during the test\n  - Avoids adding a heavy Hadoop dependency or direct reflection in the test\n\nFiles changed:\n\n- `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org_apache_parquet/parquet_common/CompressionCodecNameTest.java`\n- `tests/src/org.apache.parquet/parquet-common/1.12.2/src/test/java/org/apache/hadoop/io/compress/GzipCodec.java`\n\nPer instruction, I did not compile or run tests locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_003e761b055dc0310169f56347db208196ab324ed7e68bbddb\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 774, "output": 919, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24733, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777689403740, "responseId": "resp_003e761b055dc0310169f5633c34ac8196b7db28756a35863e"}, "toolResults": []}
